-- Sarkozy Tied With Hollande in First Round, Le Figaro Poll Shows
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2012-03-17T09:01:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/sarkozy-tied-with-hollande-in-first-round-le-figaro-poll-shows.html
Nicolas Sarkozy  has gained ground
on his Socialist challenger  Francois Hollande , with the two tied
at 27.5 percent apiece for the first round of French
presidential voting on April 22, according to a poll published
today by Le Figaro.  The poll, conducted by OpinionWay-Fiducial for Le Figaro
and cable news channel LCI, shows Hollande would beat Sarkozy by
55 percent to 45 percent in the second round on May 6, the
newspaper said. According to the poll, National Front candidate
Marine Le Pen would draw 16 percent of the first-round vote, and
46 percent of her supporters say they havenâ€™t decided whom to
vote for in the second round.  To contact the reporter on this story:
